               <history>
                  <provenance>Offsets of two coats of arms on fol. 4r.</provenance>
                  <provenance>In the calendar on 7 February is added the obit of Christine
                     ux[oris] J. Benet</provenance>
                  <provenance>Additions in English in the calendar, probably all from the first half of the sixteenth century, indicating the
                     dates of fairs in many places in Yorkshire and the midlands: e.g. Barnsley, 25 Jan. (fair chartered 1514)</provenance>
                  <provenance>Constable family (?): addition in the calendar of the birth of William Constable at Kinoulton (Notts.), 7 June 1532; and obit (?) of William Constable, 19 April.</provenance>
                  <provenance>Poem in English added, early 17th century, fol. 1r, on the death of Henry Frederick, prince of Wales in 1612 (beg. 'Tymes greedie hand ...'); not in Folger First Line Index..</provenance>
                  <provenance notAfter="1707" resp="#MMM">
                     <persName key="person_2867" role="fmo">Henry Jones, -1707</persName>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition resp="#MMM" when="1708">Received by the Bodleian, 1708.</acquisition>
               </history>
